From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <dpaa1@vyos-ls1046a-build>
Date: Sat, 30 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dpaa: HW VLAN-strip via .ndo_set_features -> fman_hm_node_install (M3-3c bridge)

The productive FMan Header-Manipulation install body (board patch 0099,
fman_hm_node_install/destroy in dpaa_fman_caps.c) is dormant on dpaa1:
it is an EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL kernel-C entry point with no userspace caller.
Spec sec 5.5 names the intended consumer for the default flavor -- back
NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX in dev->features so the stack sees pre-stripped
frames -- but nothing wired it. This patch is that bridge (the true
prerequisite for the vyos-1x 'set interfaces ethernet ethX hw-offload
vlan-strip' CLI, which only drives 'ethtool -K ethX rxvlan on').

What this adds
--------------
- dpaa_eth.h: struct dpaa_priv gains u32 hm_vlan_strip_handle (0 = not
  installed) to hold the HMTD MURAM offset returned by the install body.

- dpaa_eth.c dpaa_netdev_init(): advertise NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX in
  net_dev->hw_features, gated on fman_hm_caps_supported() so the knob only
  appears on ucode-210 boards (caps 0x17 on the Mono Gateway DK). On
  mainline-ucode boards the feature is never advertised, so the enable
  path is unreachable and ethtool cannot request an -ENOTSUPP install.

- dpaa_eth.c dpaa_set_features(): new .ndo_set_features handler. On a
  0->1 transition of NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX it installs a single-op HM
  node {num_ops=1, ops[0].type=FMAN_HM_OP_VLAN_STRIP} and stores the
  handle; on 1->0 it destroys it. struct fman * and the FMan port id are
  resolved with existing in-tree APIs: fman_bind(mac_dev->fman_dev) for
  the struct fman *, and fman_port_get_qman_channel_id(mac_dev->port[RX])
  (the same getter the driver already uses in dpaa_fq_setup()) for the
  opaque per-port id the install body forwards to fman_pcd_hm_install().
  No-op when the requested state already matches. Wired into dpaa_ops next
  to .ndo_xsk_wakeup.

No new includes: dpaa_eth.c already pulls in dpaa_fman_caps.h (the HM API
+ struct fman_hm_spec), fman.h (fman_bind), fman_port.h
(fman_port_get_qman_channel_id), and mac.h (struct mac_device, RX enum).

Byte-identical to mainline on boards without HM caps. Spec sec 5.5.

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <dpaa1@vyos-ls1046a-build>
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
index dcfd075..6505142 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
@@ -232,6 +232,17 @@ static int dpaa_netdev_init(struct net_device *net_dev,
 				 NETIF_F_RXHASH);
 
 	net_dev->hw_features |= NETIF_F_SG | NETIF_F_HIGHDMA;
+
+	/* HM offload (spec sec 5.5): on ucode-210 boards the FMan
+	 * Header-Manipulation engine can strip a VLAN tag in hardware.
+	 * Advertise NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX so the stack (and the VyOS
+	 * 'set interfaces ethernet ethX hw-offload vlan-strip' CLI via
+	 * 'ethtool -K ethX rxvlan on') can toggle it; dpaa_set_features()
+	 * installs/destroys the HM node. Gated on the runtime HM cap so
+	 * mainline-ucode boards never expose a knob that would -ENOTSUPP.
+	 */
+	if (fman_hm_caps_supported())
+		net_dev->hw_features |= NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX;
 	/* The kernels enables GSO automatically, if we declare NETIF_F_SG.
 	 * For conformity, we'll still declare GSO explicitly.
 	 */
@@ -3429,6 +3440,67 @@ static int dpaa_xsk_wakeup(struct net_device *ndev, u32 queue_id, u32 flags)
 	return ret;
 }
 
+/* HM VLAN-strip offload bridge (spec sec 5.5, board patch 0101).
+ *
+ * .ndo_set_features handler: when the stack flips NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX
+ * (e.g. 'ethtool -K ethX rxvlan on/off', driven by the VyOS
+ * 'set interfaces ethernet ethX hw-offload vlan-strip' CLI), install or
+ * destroy a single-op FMan HM node that strips one VLAN tag at L2
+ * offset 12.  The struct fman * and FMan port id are resolved with
+ * existing in-tree APIs: fman_bind(priv->mac_dev->fman_dev) and
+ * fman_port_get_qman_channel_id(priv->mac_dev->port[RX]).  The returned
+ * HMTD MURAM offset is
+ * stashed in priv->hm_vlan_strip_handle (0 = not installed).
+ *
+ * Fail-soft: on a board without FMAN_CAP_HM_NODES the feature was never
+ * advertised (see dpaa_netdev_init()), so the enable branch is
+ * unreachable; should it ever run, fman_hm_node_install() returns
+ * -ENOTSUPP and we propagate it so the ethtool set fails cleanly.
+ */
+static int dpaa_set_features(struct net_device *net_dev,
+    netdev_features_t features)
+{
+struct dpaa_priv *priv = netdev_priv(net_dev);
+bool want_strip = !!(features & NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX);
+bool have_strip = priv->hm_vlan_strip_handle != 0;
+struct fman *fm;
+u8 port_id;
+int err;
+
+if (want_strip == have_strip)
+return 0;
+
+if (!priv->mac_dev)
+return -ENODEV;
+
+fm = fman_bind(priv->mac_dev->fman_dev);
+if (!fm)
+return -ENODEV;
+port_id = (u8)fman_port_get_qman_channel_id(priv->mac_dev->port[RX]);
+
+if (want_strip) {
+struct fman_hm_spec spec = {
+.num_ops = 1,
+.ops[0] = { .type = FMAN_HM_OP_VLAN_STRIP },
+};
+u32 handle = 0;
+
+err = fman_hm_node_install(fm, port_id, &spec, &handle);
+if (err) {
+netif_err(priv, drv, net_dev,
+  "hw vlan-strip install failed: %d\n", err);
+return err;
+}
+priv->hm_vlan_strip_handle = handle;
+} else {
+fman_hm_node_destroy(fm, port_id,
+     priv->hm_vlan_strip_handle);
+priv->hm_vlan_strip_handle = 0;
+}
+
+return 0;
+}
+
 static const struct net_device_ops dpaa_ops = {
 	.ndo_open = dpaa_open,
 	.ndo_start_xmit = dpaa_start_xmit,
@@ -3444,6 +3515,7 @@ static const struct net_device_ops dpaa_ops = {
 	.ndo_bpf = dpaa_xdp,
 	.ndo_xdp_xmit = dpaa_xdp_xmit,
 	.ndo_xsk_wakeup = dpaa_xsk_wakeup,
+.ndo_set_features = dpaa_set_features,
 	.ndo_hwtstamp_get = dpaa_hwtstamp_get,
 	.ndo_hwtstamp_set = dpaa_hwtstamp_set,
 };
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.h b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.h
index 5ad97f9..d9b782f 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.h
@@ -188,6 +188,11 @@ struct dpaa_priv {
 
 	u8 num_tc;
 	bool keygen_in_use;
+/* HM VLAN-strip node handle (0 = not installed). Bridges
+ * NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX -> fman_hm_node_install(VLAN_STRIP).
+ * Spec sec 5.5; board patch 0101.
+ */
+u32 hm_vlan_strip_handle;
 	u32 msg_enable;	/* net_device message level */
 
 	struct {
-- 
2.39.5
